@Node Description "Description"

  Description
  ===========

    The check corrupt door is called by CheckFiles just after the
    file id has been checked (so that users can give descriptions
    to corrupt files!)

    It uses external checker programs to check files, based on
    the extension of the file.

    Files with NO extension are not checked for corruption.

@EndNode

@Node Installation "Installation"

  Installation
  ============

    The doors is stored as HBBS:Doors/System/Check_Corrupt/Check_Corrupt.HBBS

    This is included and enabled with a fresh installation of HydraBBS
    since V1.04.  Users of prior version should do this:

    Add the following lines to the appropriate "commands/system" file:

    Check_Corrupt_Type_1=HBBS
    Check_Corrupt_Door_1=HBBS:Doors/System/Check_Corrupt/Check_Corrupt.HBBS {N} {O}

    See HBBS:Storage/Example_Configs/Commands/System for an example

@EndNode

